name: Brie Cups
author: EHS
summary: If you are looking for a quick, easy, delicious appetizer, this is for you. I've served them many times and my friends always gobble them up. Even cheese haters love this. You can find the phyllo cups in the freezer section.
ingredients: 1 (8 ounce) wedge Brie cheese, rind removed, cut into 1-inch pieces
½ cup raspberry preserves, or to taste
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Line a baking sheet with parchment paper
Arrange phyllo cups on the baking sheet
Place one piece Brie cheese in each phyllo cup
Bake in the preheated oven until Brie is melted, about 7 minutes
